1
00:00:06,244 --> 00:00:09,815
(Kim Ye Rim)

2
00:00:12,684 --> 00:00:16,221
(Kang Sang Jun)

3
00:00:19,524 --> 00:00:23,028
(Ko Ju Hee, Jung Hyun Min)

4
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:32,137
(Azure Spring)

5
00:00:32,137 --> 00:00:33,405
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

6
00:00:33,405 --> 00:00:34,640
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

7
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:35,874
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

8
00:00:35,874 --> 00:00:37,109
(for filming child actors and animals.)

9
00:02:11,670 --> 00:02:12,604
Go!

10
00:02:12,604 --> 00:02:13,639
And they're off!

11
00:02:13,639 --> 00:02:16,375
Han Ye Kyung of South Korea
makes a perfectly clean dive.

12
00:02:16,875 --> 00:02:18,176
Now she's breaking the surface.

13
00:02:18,176 --> 00:02:19,878
And she begins her freestyle stroke.

14
00:02:20,612 --> 00:02:22,714
Her strokes are fluid,
and her rhythm is consistent.

15
00:02:22,714 --> 00:02:25,817
She's nearing the halfway mark.

16
00:02:26,718 --> 00:02:28,320
Into the turn!

17
00:02:29,021 --> 00:02:29,988
Looking good!

18
00:02:29,988 --> 00:02:32,124
Perfect touch on the wall,
and a smooth change of direction.

19
00:02:32,124 --> 00:02:34,159
She's picking up the pace with ease.

20
00:02:34,426 --> 00:02:37,095
And now heading into the final ten meters!

21
00:02:37,095 --> 00:02:38,497
Han Ye Kyung.

22
00:02:38,497 --> 00:02:40,732
Han Ye Kyung! Touches!

23
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:42,634
First place!

24
00:02:42,634 --> 00:02:45,003
It's a gold medal! Gold medal!

25
00:02:45,637 --> 00:02:46,939
What an unbelievable moment!

26
00:02:46,939 --> 00:02:50,275
Gold has returned
to Korean women's swimming.

27
00:02:50,642 --> 00:02:52,978
A rising star and a true dark horse,

28
00:02:52,978 --> 00:02:55,847
Han Ye Kyung finally makes her mark.

29
00:02:55,847 --> 00:02:56,615
Thank you.

30
00:02:56,615 --> 00:02:59,251
What a proud moment for Han Ye Kyung!

31
00:02:59,518 --> 00:03:02,621
We are living in the era of Han Ye Kyung.

32
00:03:03,288 --> 00:03:04,122
(Han Ye Kyung: New National Record
Women's Swimming, South Korea)

33
00:03:04,122 --> 00:03:05,891
Dreams do come true.

34
00:03:06,625 --> 00:03:10,362
(Han Ye Kyung: New National Record
Women's Swimming, South Korea)

35
00:03:11,563 --> 00:03:12,431
Of course,

36
00:03:13,432 --> 00:03:15,300
it doesn't necessarily
have to be my dream.

37
00:03:41,259 --> 00:03:48,233
(Episode 1
Rise or Fall, We're Still Young)

38
00:04:33,278 --> 00:04:34,880
"Pa" for waves, and "Rang" for beauty.

39
00:04:35,814 --> 00:04:37,783
Parang-ri,
where the ripples are beautiful,

40
00:04:38,150 --> 00:04:39,785
even in the mountainous Namhae region,

41
00:04:39,785 --> 00:04:41,520
is a village famous
for its shimmering ripples.

42
00:04:45,090 --> 00:04:46,725
Beyond the edge of Tongyeong,
you have to take a boat...

43
00:04:46,725 --> 00:04:49,628
an hour deeper into the sea
to find this backwater village.

44
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:55,801
This is...

45
00:04:56,668 --> 00:04:57,769
my hometown.

46
00:05:34,172 --> 00:05:35,073
This is tiring.

47
00:06:13,011 --> 00:06:14,279
It's been five years,

48
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:16,315
and why is it so spotless?

49
00:06:17,749 --> 00:06:19,251
No need for any cleaning.

50
00:08:13,365 --> 00:08:16,134
Mom never used the iron pot.

51
00:08:17,069 --> 00:08:18,403
After a long day of diving,

52
00:08:18,403 --> 00:08:20,339
hauling over a hundred pounds of seafood,

53
00:08:20,872 --> 00:08:23,208
coming home to this heavy pot...

54
00:08:23,609 --> 00:08:26,945
to lift it, scrub it,
and even grease it down...

55
00:08:27,579 --> 00:08:28,680
was something she refused to do.

56
00:08:38,523 --> 00:08:40,058
But once a year,

57
00:08:40,359 --> 00:08:41,526
on my birthday...

58
00:08:41,526 --> 00:08:43,996
she'd fill this very pot
with the seaweed she'd caught that day...

59
00:08:43,996 --> 00:08:45,397
and cook me seaweed soup.

60
00:09:07,619 --> 00:09:08,754
This is unusual.

61
00:09:09,321 --> 00:09:10,889
At home, for the first time
in a long while,

62
00:09:11,690 --> 00:09:14,626
of all things, I cook seaweed soup
in this iron pot.

63
00:09:16,828 --> 00:09:17,663
Seo Anna.

64
00:09:18,230 --> 00:09:19,097
Happy birthday.

65
00:10:05,043 --> 00:10:06,812
Just living in hiding like this...

66
00:10:07,813 --> 00:10:09,247
might not be that bad.

67
00:10:34,539 --> 00:10:35,540
This is the person!

68
00:10:36,642 --> 00:10:38,243
I told you before, don't you remember?

69
00:10:41,613 --> 00:10:42,914
Good grief.

70
00:10:43,315 --> 00:10:44,850
(Parang Harbor Fishermen's Association)

71
00:10:44,850 --> 00:10:45,684
Where is it?

72
00:10:46,451 --> 00:10:47,286
Here!

73
00:10:47,819 --> 00:10:48,687
Take a look.

74
00:10:50,689 --> 00:10:52,524
- Thanks for the effort.
- Thank you.

75
00:10:53,925 --> 00:10:55,827
There's a kid looking for a room
in the village.

76
00:10:55,827 --> 00:10:57,596
Is it okay to rent out your mom's house?

77
00:10:59,031 --> 00:11:00,432
Just let the person live there.

78
00:11:00,432 --> 00:11:01,800
Having someone in an empty house...

79
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,001
is good for upkeep and all.

80
00:11:04,770 --> 00:11:06,605
(Just let the person live there.)

81
00:11:08,874 --> 00:11:09,708
See?

82
00:11:11,043 --> 00:11:12,411
Anna, are you going to stay long?

83
00:11:14,546 --> 00:11:15,781
Aren't you going to swim anymore?

84
00:11:15,781 --> 00:11:17,215
Who says I'm not? I'm still swimming!

85
00:11:17,749 --> 00:11:19,418
There's no need to snap.

86
00:11:20,419 --> 00:11:22,087
If you're just visiting
for a little while,

87
00:11:22,087 --> 00:11:24,756
then you could stay together like family.

88
00:11:25,324 --> 00:11:26,758
It's not like we're living
in the dark ages.

89
00:11:27,092 --> 00:11:28,694
You've got plenty of rooms,
so what's the big deal?

90
00:11:28,694 --> 00:11:29,594
Chief.

91
00:11:30,262 --> 00:11:32,197
There's no need to be afraid of him.

92
00:11:33,398 --> 00:11:34,800
That was a frost-bound stare.

93
00:11:35,734 --> 00:11:38,270
Anyway, you young folks...

94
00:11:38,270 --> 00:11:41,139
figure this out.

95
00:11:41,139 --> 00:11:42,007
Got it?

96
00:11:42,474 --> 00:11:43,408
Good.

97
00:11:43,842 --> 00:11:44,810
You two look good together.

98
00:11:45,877 --> 00:11:47,946
Something's going to happen for sure.

99
00:11:54,019 --> 00:11:55,220
Now that it's come to this,

100
00:11:56,421 --> 00:11:57,956
let's just make the best of it together.

101
00:11:59,491 --> 00:12:01,893
Tenant in the guest house,
me in the main house.

102
00:12:02,427 --> 00:12:04,096
As long as we don't bother each other.

103
00:12:04,429 --> 00:12:06,331
Even if you hear the phone,
act like you didn't.

104
00:12:06,331 --> 00:12:08,133
Even if you see what I'm eating,
pretend not to see.

105
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:09,635
Even if we're living under the same roof,

106
00:12:09,635 --> 00:12:11,036
just like living alone, basically.

107
00:12:11,603 --> 00:12:12,704
What do you say, Mr. Tenant?

108
00:12:19,211 --> 00:12:20,412
Well? Nothing to say?

109
00:12:21,213 --> 00:12:23,882
Are you with me on this?

110
00:12:23,882 --> 00:12:24,950
Or are you out?

111
00:12:25,417 --> 00:12:26,652
Will you be staying long?

112
00:12:28,287 --> 00:12:30,289
First the village chief, and now you...

113
00:12:30,289 --> 00:12:32,124
why does everyone keep asking me
how long I'll be here?

114
00:12:32,624 --> 00:12:33,458
Very long...

115
00:12:33,759 --> 00:12:34,993
for a very, very long time.

116
00:12:35,427 --> 00:12:36,328
Forever.

117
00:12:36,662 --> 00:12:38,096
I really hope so.

118
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:42,968
Did you just blow me off?

119
00:12:44,569 --> 00:12:45,437
Hey.

120
00:12:45,937 --> 00:12:46,805
Hey!

121
00:12:51,410 --> 00:12:52,277
Hey!

122
00:12:53,779 --> 00:12:54,746
Seo Anna!

123
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,615
It's you, right?

124
00:12:57,149 --> 00:12:57,950
Who are you?

125
00:12:59,284 --> 00:13:00,385
It's really you.

126
00:13:00,652 --> 00:13:03,622
The Mermaid of Parang-ri, Seo Anna!

127
00:13:04,823 --> 00:13:06,591
It's been years.

128
00:13:06,591 --> 00:13:08,026
Mermaid, what?

129
00:13:09,628 --> 00:13:11,496
Do you remember me?

130
00:13:13,966 --> 00:13:16,735
The Trot Goddess of Parang-ri.

131
00:13:16,735 --> 00:13:18,370
Baek Su Jeong!

132
00:13:18,971 --> 00:13:22,407
Oh, my goodness
Oh, my goodness, don't do this

133
00:13:22,975 --> 00:13:26,912
A woman's heart is like a reed

134
00:13:27,179 --> 00:13:30,749
Don't do this, what's wrong with you?
Don't ask me

135
00:13:31,383 --> 00:13:35,921
You can't want me anymore

136
00:13:37,089 --> 00:13:40,692
Today it's the first time I met you

137
00:13:46,798 --> 00:13:49,234
Who dares to run away
while the Trot Goddess of Parang-ri...

138
00:13:49,234 --> 00:13:50,636
is performing?

139
00:13:50,869 --> 00:13:51,903
Sorry.

140
00:13:52,738 --> 00:13:54,906
I've got swimming practice.

141
00:13:55,841 --> 00:13:57,943
Fair enough, the Little Mermaid
needs her swim training.

142
00:13:58,343 --> 00:13:59,978
Have a great time! Keep it up!

143
00:14:00,479 --> 00:14:01,480
Okay, got it.

144
00:14:03,448 --> 00:14:04,416
Now, focus.

145
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:05,350
I'll start over.

146
00:14:06,184 --> 00:14:09,755
Oh, my goodness
Oh, my goodness, don't do this

147
00:14:13,692 --> 00:14:14,793
I'm doomed.

148
00:14:17,362 --> 00:14:18,964
So much for living on my own.

149
00:14:19,731 --> 00:14:22,301
Truly, a singer's voice
is their fingerprint.

150
00:14:22,601 --> 00:14:24,970
I guess you remembered me
as soon as you heard the song?

151
00:14:26,171 --> 00:14:27,039
I knew it.

152
00:14:27,839 --> 00:14:29,708
And so much for living a quiet life.

153
00:14:30,175 --> 00:14:31,109
And so,

154
00:14:31,410 --> 00:14:33,145
I heard you went to Seoul
to be a competitive swimmer.

155
00:14:33,412 --> 00:14:34,646
Why are you back out of the blue?

156
00:14:37,649 --> 00:14:38,517
Well...

157
00:14:39,017 --> 00:14:40,786
The Parang-ri Mermaid,
who was said to be a swimmer in Seoul,

158
00:14:41,119 --> 00:14:42,788
is actually...

159
00:14:53,265 --> 00:14:54,433
My goodness...

160
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,702
you look tired these days.

161
00:14:57,202 --> 00:14:59,638
Your boyfriend must be quite strong?

162
00:15:01,473 --> 00:15:02,374
What?

163
00:15:02,374 --> 00:15:04,876
I said, your boyfriend
must be quite strong.

164
00:15:04,876 --> 00:15:05,777
Tidy up here.

165
00:15:09,948 --> 00:15:11,516
Little Mermaid? Yeah, right.

166
00:15:13,652 --> 00:15:16,822
I'm no longer the Parang-ri Mermaid.

167
00:15:22,527 --> 00:15:24,229
Hey, stop. Stay still.

168
00:15:24,229 --> 00:15:25,097
Don't move.

169
00:15:25,464 --> 00:15:26,665
Hey, don't move.

170
00:15:27,466 --> 00:15:29,001
Today, your...

171
00:15:30,435 --> 00:15:32,404
your booty is in top shape.

172
00:15:33,005 --> 00:15:36,108
One little brush against this,

173
00:15:36,475 --> 00:15:38,010
it feels like it's about to snap.

174
00:15:39,077 --> 00:15:39,978
Hey!

175
00:15:42,948 --> 00:15:45,117
Hey. Did you just say "hey" to me?

176
00:15:45,384 --> 00:15:46,251
You heard me. I said "hey."

177
00:15:46,251 --> 00:15:48,020
What! You creep!

178
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:50,289
- I'm going to kill you!
- Watch your language with me.

179
00:15:50,989 --> 00:15:53,492
You're lucky I'm letting this slide today.

180
00:15:54,259 --> 00:15:56,194
- You are so dead.
- Wait.

181
00:15:57,396 --> 00:15:58,563
Hey, my nose is bleeding.

182
00:16:00,399 --> 00:16:01,733
Hey, Seo Anna.

183
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:04,403
Don't bother coming in from tomorrow!

184
00:16:06,371 --> 00:16:07,940
You're fired!

185
00:16:26,191 --> 00:16:27,926
It's been a while
since I've actually swum.

186
00:16:28,994 --> 00:16:30,862
I just worked a part-time job at a pool,
but I lost it.

187
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:36,802
There's no need to
tell this to Parang-ri's...

188
00:16:37,402 --> 00:16:39,004
chatterbox, Baek Su Jeong.

189
00:16:40,439 --> 00:16:41,440
Why are you back?

190
00:16:42,774 --> 00:16:45,310
I mean, why are you here?

191
00:16:46,078 --> 00:16:46,945
Just.

192
00:16:48,213 --> 00:16:49,281
It's just so unfair.

193
00:16:49,281 --> 00:16:50,115
Unfair?

194
00:16:50,882 --> 00:16:51,717
What is?

195
00:16:53,018 --> 00:16:53,986
By the way,

196
00:16:54,553 --> 00:16:56,588
about the guy who lives in my house.

197
00:16:57,255 --> 00:16:58,523
Are you talking about Deok Hyun?

198
00:16:59,825 --> 00:17:00,692
He's older?

199
00:17:01,526 --> 00:17:02,561
Anyway.

200
00:17:02,561 --> 00:17:04,663
What's his deal?

201
00:17:06,331 --> 00:17:07,432
A male sea diver.

202
00:17:07,699 --> 00:17:09,101
- A male diver?
- Yes.

203
00:17:09,401 --> 00:17:10,802
He dives for a living.

204
00:17:11,069 --> 00:17:12,070
And he looks...

205
00:17:13,372 --> 00:17:15,140
incredibly cool doing it.

206
00:17:28,220 --> 00:17:30,422
Deok Hyun, nice!

207
00:17:33,425 --> 00:17:36,662
Though the area is a bit uphill,

208
00:17:36,895 --> 00:17:38,864
you'll be okay after a few trips.

209
00:17:39,898 --> 00:17:40,966
Nice.

210
00:17:40,966 --> 00:17:42,134
Ain't it nice?

211
00:17:44,736 --> 00:17:45,570
This place...

212
00:17:47,205 --> 00:17:48,840
has an incredible view.

213
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:51,209
His name is Yun Deok Hyun.

214
00:17:51,443 --> 00:17:53,111
Age, occupation, and past...

215
00:17:54,046 --> 00:17:55,180
unknown.

216
00:17:55,180 --> 00:17:57,816
Out of nowhere one day...

217
00:17:59,084 --> 00:18:01,987
Drifted in like the wind

218
00:18:01,987 --> 00:18:03,889
A mysterious young man

219
00:18:05,791 --> 00:18:06,625
Wait.

220
00:18:07,392 --> 00:18:08,360
No way...

221
00:18:09,494 --> 00:18:11,163
are you interested in Deok Hyun too?

222
00:18:11,630 --> 00:18:12,531
Too?

223
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:17,869
Don't tell me you're interested in him.

224
00:18:19,905 --> 00:18:21,106
You tell me first.

225
00:18:21,373 --> 00:18:23,008
Weren't you only staying for a short bit?

226
00:18:23,008 --> 00:18:24,409
Aren't you going to swim?

227
00:18:24,409 --> 00:18:26,345
I am. I'm going to.

228
00:18:26,511 --> 00:18:28,013
Why are you being like this too?

229
00:18:28,714 --> 00:18:30,882
Plus, I'm not interested in him at all.

230
00:18:32,317 --> 00:18:33,852
What's there to like about such a jerk?

231
00:18:34,553 --> 00:18:36,388
A jerk?

232
00:18:37,155 --> 00:18:39,591
A young male diver shrouded in mystery.

233
00:18:40,626 --> 00:18:42,461
Isn't that too sexy?

234
00:18:44,663 --> 00:18:45,631
Sexy?

235
00:19:11,456 --> 00:19:13,458
What part of him is even remotely sexy?

236
00:19:13,458 --> 00:19:14,893
He's just dark and tanned, that's all.

237
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:20,299
Oh, you got a baby sea bream there?

238
00:19:20,299 --> 00:19:21,900
That'll be so tasty in a soup.

239
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,302
Didn't we agree...

240
00:19:23,302 --> 00:19:25,470
to just look the other way
regarding what we eat?

241
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:30,809
I'm just saying, that's all.

242
00:19:31,910 --> 00:19:34,379
Like I said, baby sea bream
is really good in soup.

243
00:19:35,314 --> 00:19:36,248
Information!

244
00:19:46,124 --> 00:19:47,225
Sexy? Sure.

245
00:19:48,026 --> 00:19:49,461
He's a snotty scumbag.

246
00:19:51,630 --> 00:19:53,165
What the...

247
00:20:18,156 --> 00:20:19,658
This middle-of-nowhere village.

248
00:20:20,359 --> 00:20:22,227
Eating is the only joy.

249
00:20:25,664 --> 00:20:26,698
Wake up, Seo Anna.

250
00:20:27,466 --> 00:20:29,034
Like he'd actually give it to me
if I asked.

251
00:20:29,334 --> 00:20:30,602
Have you no pride?

252
00:21:07,139 --> 00:21:08,840
(Snack Bar
Sea Squirt &amp; Pork Belly Available)

253
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:10,475
(Ramyeon, Gimbap, Noodles)

254
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,481
What kind of snack bar closes at seven?

255
00:21:29,962 --> 00:21:31,063
Why aren't you answering my calls?

256
00:21:31,396 --> 00:21:32,731
Don't tell me you blocked me?

257
00:21:33,799 --> 00:21:36,301
Are you unaware of how tight
the owner is with the association?

258
00:21:37,536 --> 00:21:39,504
Are you going to quit swimming for good?

259
00:21:39,504 --> 00:21:40,339
(Ignore xxx)

260
00:21:50,182 --> 00:21:51,683
Where did all that sparkle go?

261
00:21:53,051 --> 00:21:54,386
It's just pitch black now.

262
00:21:55,654 --> 00:21:58,523
It's so dark,
even a ghost could hide.

263
00:22:21,179 --> 00:22:22,114
I'm hungry.

264
00:22:43,035 --> 00:22:44,102
Mr. Tenant!

265
00:22:46,038 --> 00:22:46,972
Anybody there?

266
00:22:51,810 --> 00:22:52,678
Is he gone?

267
00:22:54,413 --> 00:22:55,714
Excuse me.

268
00:23:01,119 --> 00:23:02,220
You out?

269
00:23:10,429 --> 00:23:11,797
Wow, so organized.

270
00:23:12,631 --> 00:23:13,899
Typical. This says everything about him.

271
00:23:21,707 --> 00:23:23,508
Where did he hide it?

272
00:23:34,319 --> 00:23:37,022
Never lose that food radar, Seo Anna.

273
00:23:48,266 --> 00:23:49,201
Sea squirts?

274
00:23:49,968 --> 00:23:51,603
Why did he freeze these beauties?

275
00:23:52,037 --> 00:23:53,939
Should've mixed in a bowl of rice
right then and there.

276
00:23:56,308 --> 00:23:57,476
Well, I guess I'll have to
eat them myself.

277
00:24:00,279 --> 00:24:02,881
(Parang-ri)

278
00:24:02,881 --> 00:24:04,683
Chief, I'd like to use the field a bit.

279
00:24:04,683 --> 00:24:05,917
Do as you please.

280
00:25:01,707 --> 00:25:03,375
Nothing soothes you in the morning...

281
00:25:03,375 --> 00:25:06,078
like a bowl of clear fish soup.

282
00:25:09,014 --> 00:25:11,950
If you make that clear fish soup
with pufferfish, it's pufferfish soup.

283
00:25:12,351 --> 00:25:14,620
And if you use a baby sea bream,
like me right now...

284
00:25:15,020 --> 00:25:16,455
then it becomes baby sea bream soup.

285
00:25:50,589 --> 00:25:53,492
The classic way for sea squirt
is mixing it on the spot with rice,

286
00:25:53,492 --> 00:25:55,694
lettuce, and a dash of sesame oil.

287
00:25:56,995 --> 00:25:58,630
Still, sea squirts
that missed their timing...

288
00:25:59,197 --> 00:26:01,833
can be a real treat
when made into pancakes.

289
00:26:18,951 --> 00:26:21,253
When ingredients are iffy,

290
00:26:21,253 --> 00:26:22,554
Rule one of solo living...

291
00:26:26,358 --> 00:26:27,326
oil is the answer.

292
00:27:35,627 --> 00:27:36,528
I should...

293
00:27:37,963 --> 00:27:39,031
go back, right?

294
00:27:49,241 --> 00:27:51,476
Does sharing the kitchen
include sharing the food too?

295
00:27:52,477 --> 00:27:53,412
Gosh, you scared me.

296
00:27:57,549 --> 00:27:58,483
Well, you see...

297
00:27:59,017 --> 00:28:00,252
I thought you'd thrown them away.

298
00:28:01,286 --> 00:28:03,588
Then, they'd be in the trash,

299
00:28:03,588 --> 00:28:04,656
not the freezer.

300
00:28:06,892 --> 00:28:09,795
It's just fish scraps and sea squirt.
Don't be so cheap about it.

301
00:28:10,228 --> 00:28:11,897
Do you think catching sea squirts is easy?

302
00:28:12,898 --> 00:28:14,633
Don't act so special
just because you dive.

303
00:28:15,734 --> 00:28:18,070
I was quite a swimmer myself, you know.

304
00:28:18,337 --> 00:28:19,838
You're using the past tense,

305
00:28:19,838 --> 00:28:21,139
so I guess you no longer...

306
00:28:23,542 --> 00:28:24,376
swim.

307
00:28:26,011 --> 00:28:27,446
- What?
- Or...

308
00:28:28,213 --> 00:28:29,214
you can't.

309
00:28:30,949 --> 00:28:32,818
Hey, what do you know about me?

310
00:28:32,818 --> 00:28:35,053
Whatever it is, it'll be best
to make up your mind soon.

311
00:28:35,354 --> 00:28:36,254
About what?

312
00:28:37,623 --> 00:28:39,791
Whether you're going to commit
and settle down here.

313
00:28:39,791 --> 00:28:41,159
Or if you're just here for a breather...

314
00:28:41,159 --> 00:28:42,494
before going back to your old life.

315
00:28:43,629 --> 00:28:45,897
People who wallow in self-pity,

316
00:28:45,897 --> 00:28:47,666
ruin this village's mood,
and then just leave.

317
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:49,167
I've seen it all too many times.

318
00:28:52,404 --> 00:28:53,305
Information.

319
00:29:03,715 --> 00:29:04,683
Seo Anna!

320
00:29:08,353 --> 00:29:09,721
Why'd you quit your part-time job?

321
00:29:10,155 --> 00:29:12,057
Don't you know who the boss is?

322
00:29:13,625 --> 00:29:14,793
How could I not know.

323
00:29:15,460 --> 00:29:17,396
Yes, I was obsessed because
I never got Mom that gold medal,

324
00:29:17,396 --> 00:29:19,197
and so I trained
day and night without rest.

325
00:29:19,197 --> 00:29:21,300
So you pulled strings to get this job...

326
00:29:21,667 --> 00:29:23,869
for your "washed-up" girlfriend.

327
00:29:24,436 --> 00:29:26,204
You said he's close
with the association president...

328
00:29:26,204 --> 00:29:28,340
and that he could help my comeback
even after a few years off.

329
00:29:28,340 --> 00:29:29,408
You know exactly!

330
00:29:30,442 --> 00:29:31,843
But you screw up like that?

331
00:29:33,612 --> 00:29:35,380
Do you really want to ruin your life?

332
00:29:36,581 --> 00:29:38,083
How can everyone so easily judge...

333
00:29:39,518 --> 00:29:41,887
whether someone's life is ruined or not?

334
00:29:43,789 --> 00:29:45,557
As your swim coach for nine years.

335
00:29:46,358 --> 00:29:47,960
As your boyfriend for three years.

336
00:29:49,494 --> 00:29:51,863
Anna, I've known you for 12 years.

337
00:29:53,098 --> 00:29:53,932
Right?

338
00:29:55,867 --> 00:29:57,302
Are you done with swimming?

339
00:29:58,103 --> 00:30:01,073
Do you want your name
to stay as Seo Anna, the failed prospect?

340
00:30:10,849 --> 00:30:11,750
Seo Anna.

341
00:30:12,918 --> 00:30:14,019
This is my last warning.

342
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:16,288
Put down the suitcase.

343
00:30:18,457 --> 00:30:19,558
Jerks.

344
00:30:20,392 --> 00:30:21,360
You're going to pay for this.

345
00:30:27,466 --> 00:30:28,600
Where did he go?

346
00:31:26,458 --> 00:31:27,726
Since when was there a sea like this...

347
00:31:29,594 --> 00:31:30,929
hidden behind Parang-ri?

348
00:31:37,369 --> 00:31:38,136
What?

349
00:31:38,537 --> 00:31:39,304
What's that!

350
00:32:40,632 --> 00:32:42,034
Rise or fall, we're still young.

351
00:32:43,302 --> 00:32:45,704
Thank you.

352
00:32:45,971 --> 00:32:47,172
Silence.

353
00:32:47,706 --> 00:32:48,674
Enough eating.

354
00:32:48,674 --> 00:32:49,608
Everyone focus.

355
00:32:50,108 --> 00:32:51,810
Our Korea National Sport University.

356
00:32:52,611 --> 00:32:53,578
Our ace,

357
00:32:54,246 --> 00:32:55,580
Ye Kyung will give a toast.

358
00:32:57,082 --> 00:32:58,283
Our ace.

359
00:32:58,684 --> 00:33:02,587
Ace!

360
00:33:03,221 --> 00:33:04,222
I'll go with...

361
00:33:05,424 --> 00:33:07,426
"Rise or fall, we're still young!"

362
00:33:08,060 --> 00:33:09,227
Rise or fall!

363
00:33:09,227 --> 00:33:11,496
We're still young!

364
00:33:13,932 --> 00:33:15,567
- Bottoms up.
- Okay.

365
00:33:16,201 --> 00:33:17,135
Eat up.

366
00:33:17,135 --> 00:33:18,637
Even this isn't enough.

367
00:33:27,379 --> 00:33:30,415
They say, "Rise or fall,
we're still young."

368
00:33:35,020 --> 00:33:38,323
But the youth I knew wasn't like that.

369
00:33:54,773 --> 00:33:56,008
Success is youth,

370
00:34:00,412 --> 00:34:03,615
but failure is just pathetic.

371
00:34:14,860 --> 00:34:17,996
That's why I hate being called a failure.

372
00:34:19,064 --> 00:34:20,499
I fought just as hard as anyone else.

373
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:22,701
No,

374
00:34:23,168 --> 00:34:24,870
maybe I fought even harder than they did.

375
00:34:44,389 --> 00:34:45,290
What is it?

376
00:34:46,058 --> 00:34:47,125
How did you find this place?

377
00:34:53,398 --> 00:34:54,599
Teach me how to dive too.

378
00:34:58,537 --> 00:34:59,404
What?

379
00:34:59,871 --> 00:35:01,807
Let's just say the fish heads were trash,

380
00:35:02,274 --> 00:35:04,343
but I'll make up for the sea squirts.
I'll dive for them.

381
00:35:06,845 --> 00:35:08,313
It was just a passing remark.

382
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:09,548
Forget about it.

383
00:35:11,216 --> 00:35:12,084
Hey!

384
00:35:15,887 --> 00:35:18,790
Who blabs about someone's life
being ruined as a passing remark?

385
00:35:19,825 --> 00:35:20,959
I'm a good swimmer.

386
00:35:21,493 --> 00:35:24,162
I was even a national youth athlete.

387
00:35:25,097 --> 00:35:27,165
If you show me how,

388
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:30,035
I'll get those sea squirts for you.

389
00:35:31,870 --> 00:35:32,971
So,

390
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:35,907
teach me how...

391
00:35:36,942 --> 00:35:37,909
to dive.

392
00:35:42,080 --> 00:35:43,248
My life isn't ruined.

393
00:35:45,117 --> 00:35:46,351
Parang-ri Mermaid...

394
00:35:46,885 --> 00:35:48,186
isn't washed up yet.

395
00:35:59,064 --> 00:35:59,931
(Mi Hyun's daughter)

396
00:35:59,931 --> 00:36:01,400
Just let the person live there.

397
00:36:03,135 --> 00:36:04,236
She says just live here.

398
00:36:06,104 --> 00:36:06,972
Okay.

399
00:36:07,372 --> 00:36:08,774
But I'll still pay the rent.

400
00:36:10,609 --> 00:36:12,311
Make yourself at home.

401
00:36:13,712 --> 00:36:16,648
You can use a room in the main house
or the guest house.

402
00:36:37,869 --> 00:36:39,504
She looks like a real handful.

403
00:37:41,333 --> 00:37:43,335
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
